SEARCH IN A 2D MATRIX

You are given an N × M matrix with the following properties:

Each row is sorted in ascending order
The first element of each row is greater than the last element of the previous row

Your task is to determine whether a given target value exists in the matrix.

Your solution must be faster than O(N + M) time complexity.

INPUT FORMAT

The first line contains two integers N and M
N is the number of rows
M is the number of columns

The next N lines each contain M space-separated integers representing the matrix

The last line contains a single integer Target

OUTPUT FORMAT

Print YES if the target exists in the matrix
Print NO otherwise

CONSTRAINTS

1 ≤ N, M ≤ 100
-10000 ≤ matrix[i][j], Target ≤ 10000
The matrix is non-empty and sorted

SAMPLE INPUT

3 4
1 3 5 7
10 11 16 20
23 30 34 60
3

SAMPLE OUTPUT

YES

EXPLANATION

The target value 3 exists in the matrix

SAMPLE INPUT

3 4
1 3 5 7
10 11 16 20
23 30 34 60
13

SAMPLE OUTPUT

NO

EXPLANATION

The target value 13 does not exist in the matrix

import java.util.*;
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
       int n=sc.nextInt();
       int m=sc.nextInt();
       int a[][]=new int[n][m];
       for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
           for(int i=0;i<m;i++) {
               a[i][j]=sc.nextInt();
        }}  int target=sc.nextInt();
       int left=0,right=n*m-1;
       boolean f=false;
       while(left<=right){
           int mid=(left+right)/2;
           int r=mid/m;
           int c=mid%m;
           if(a[r][c]==target) {
               f=true;
               break;
           }else if(a[r][c]<target) {
               left=mid+1;
           }else{
               right=mid-1;
        } }if(f) System.out.println("YES");
       else System.out.println("NO");
}}




